Output 1. Improvement of technical standards for safe dairy production by setting up risk-sensitive demonstration model in Heilongjiang;
Output 2. Incorporation of risk management into safe dairy production model and application of good practices to entire cycle of dairy safety management;
Output 3. Policy innovation through adopting advanced management tools and innovative technologies, controlling risks through standardized processes.

Outcome 1: Improved understanding on the impacts of climate change to health; 
Outcome 2: Enhanced capacity to undertake adaptation measures in response to climatic impacts on health;
Outcome 3: Risk-conscious development planning created through enhanced cross-sectoral collaboration and coordination; 
Outcome 4: Strengthened local adaptation strategies in response to climatic disasters.
